# Feature: Example CRUD

## Board Review

- **Product (Sarah)**: Approved - this is a template placeholder demonstrating the CRUD pattern
- **Architecture (Marcus)**: Approved - clean separation of concerns across all layers
- **Security (Aisha)**: Approved - creator-only access for mutations, JWT required
- **Business (David)**: N/A - placeholder feature
- **Decision**: Go (template default)

## Business Logic

- Authenticated users can create example items
- Items have three states: DRAFT (only visible to creator), PUBLISHED (visible to all), ARCHIVED (soft-deleted)
- Only the creator or admins can update/delete items
- List endpoint supports pagination and sorting

## Entities

- [Example](../../backend/docs/entities/example.md) - the main entity
- [User](../../backend/docs/entities/user.md) - the creator

## API Endpoints

| Method | Path | Auth | Description |
|--------|------|------|-------------|
| GET | /examples | Yes | List examples (paginated) |
| POST | /examples | Yes | Create example |
| GET | /examples/{id} | Yes | Get single example |
| PUT | /examples/{id} | Yes | Update example (creator/admin only) |
| DELETE | /examples/{id} | Yes | Delete example (creator/admin only) |

